caption: Great vibes! I really like the space. Bottomless brunch is great value. You should try the biscuits, so delicious! The burger and omelette are very tasty. Service was extremely good. We will definitely w coming back.

Good food and service. Unfortunately, there were items on the menu that were not available. Granted, we appeared to be the first customers that evening and it was a rainy Wednesday. Will be returning at a later date. Hoping to try their New England clam chowder.
They serve large dishes and for convenient rates. very nice staff members. Great work.
Cozy place for a quick brunch & catch up with family/friends... prices are very budget friendly, food takes a minute to prepare but it’s quite delicious!
Great coffee, and cozy spot! Just beware when getting Lg coffee, it's a kettle full enough for a few people:)
We love Baron's. Been coming here for over 4 years. Brunch is delicious, the new fried chicken sandwich is too good. Fast and friendly service. One of our go to spots in the neighborhood.
they deliver the order too late.  i didn't like its
Excellent food and service. Although their menu is a bit more limited at this time due to the pandemic, their vegetable burger is excellent!
Nice spot for american food. Service is awesome even when they are busy. The prices are good for what you get.

NEVER AGAIN. Bartender was nice and he made a good drink. Waitress was not friendly in the slightest. The burger bun was burnt and the rest of the meal wasn't great. I did like the brussel sprout appetizers but it took a long time to come out and the main course came out about 5 minutes later, so it was more of a side. We were in and out in about 45 minutes.
Delicious
Brunch is really good. Lovely service. Prices are fair as well. Please catch a meal here before it gets too cold out.
Nice scene for american food. Entered near ten, it was not crowded. This place has a great feel to it. They have a lot of positive reviews for a reason.
Such delicious food and cocktails, great service and value.
Food was great!! Chef is a bit moody but don't sleep on the home fries they're semi crispy with limited veggies just how I like it!!!
Great service!
Good new American food and gorgeous interior... Currently offering Al fresco!
Good food, friendly staff, and their outdoor dining setup is fantastic
The service was lovely, very clean, well separated for Covid19 instructions, staff wears masks. Burger was done well, fresh - for me it was over salty.
Mushroom ravioli
Atmosphere and food were great. Service was good.
Very nice restaurant good food, unbelievable service and just go and enjoy.
Overpriced and adequate service
We are so lucky to find a table here in Valentine’s Day. Decorations was romantic and the food was perfect.

Excellent restaurant in Bed-Stuy. Come here for fantastic food and quality cocktails, all within a chique and yet relaxed atmosphere. Never once have I felt rushed while dining, the service is superb. Favorite spot in the neighborhood

Surprisingly Baron's was empty on a Sunday night. The burger was delicious, medium rare as requested. It was served with a good portion of fries, also done perfectly. Definitely recommend for a casual meal.

We love Baron’s! The lighting in the background is beautiful oranges, purples and and pinks shining through antique window panes. The staff is kind, welcoming and we loved the vegan ravioli and cocktails.
Amazing ambiance🙌 Even more amazing food. Love this place❤
Stopped by for a late drink with family. Great atmosphere. Good drink selection. Shared a beef tartar that was absolutely demolished by us (aka it was awesome). We will definitely be back.

The food was ok. I got the merquez burger and it was pretty bland. Obviously from the reviews I got the wrong thing though. We had a check in offer on yelp that they didn’t honor because we showed them after the check came but when the check came we hadn’t asked for it nor had we known it was coming. The check in offer said we had 4 hours but the manger denied us. Which was super annoying especially since the food didn’t live up to the reviews
Delicious albeit small selection of well prepared meals. Great oysters and drinks. Romantic atmosphere. Good for kids too.
Great atmosphere and food
Enjoyed my time there! Despite many reviews our wait was not long and the server was very attentive! Would recommend to my friends
great ambiance and drinks!
Really good service and the food is consistently delicious! This place is my local go-to.
Great burger, strong bellinis.  Too much salt in the vinaigrette but I will return.
Food and service were excellent to me

I had my birthday dinner at Baron's, and honestly, that was the best decision I made! Staff was really helpful from the moment I asked to make a reservation for 15 people to the moment we left the restaurant! The aura in the restaurant is fantastic; the interior design is exciting and cozy. When we arrived, our table was ready with special menus for my guests. They have a large selection of drinks, I tried three different ones, and they were all superb. The food was incredibly tasty, and the dessert was delicious too. We had a blast at Baron's; I highly recommend the place; it is one of my favorites restaurants in NYC now! My birthday dinner was spotless, thanks to the Baron's team!

It was one of those experiences where if any one of the things had happened alone, it would have been fine, but we didn’t get food for 1.5 hours after ordering, the waiter was not very friendly, lots of people who came after us got their food before us, we kept having to ask repeatedly for things, they were out of multiple items on the menu that we had wanted to order. All in all just not a good experience. The three stars come from the food actually being pretty good.
Perfect restaurant. Lovely and relaxing atmosphere. We heard about it from a friend and the food is delicious. Lovely neighbourhood Brooklyn restaurant. We loved it and we will be back

The old timey feel and relaxing atmosphere makes this place a great place for a business meeting or a relaxing afternoon with drinks. Or go for brunch and get unlimited drinks which is fantastic. A little expensive on my budget but well worth it.
Beautiful place, friendly staff and great food.  Will definitely visit again.
Tasty brunch with bottomless drinks option. They give you a pitcher for the table if you want, which is convenient. Nice, chill setting and atmosphere. Great little gem.

Attentive, friendly, warm service.  Warm interior.  Atmospheric.  Food very yummy and well composed.  Two fist pumps for the grilled calamari.  The bar in the front sector seems like it'd be a good place to soft talk some looker you're trying to pork chop.  Unintimidating drinks list.  Heckuva burger.  Just a heckuva one.  Give this place a visit!  You won't leave disappointed or unporkchopped!
Loved the vibe and amazing food, all farm to table. I had the ravioli of cashew ricotta with asparagus and mushrooms - truly delicious!! This was my first visit and I will definitely be coming back.
Went for brunch. Got a burger and fries with bottomless drinks. Burger was great. Fries delicious and drinks.... Great. I'd go back.

The food is pretty okay nothing too Wonderful buy tasty. The service was a little bit slow even though there wasn't many people around. They have a sweet deal of unlimited drinks with a selection of entree.

Great food but avoid this place like the plague if you're hungry. Every time I've come here, it's taken over 45 minutes from when I order until I get my food. That said, food is delicious here. Good prices, very friendly staff.I've had the oysters, burger, special flatbread of the day, and brick chicken. The brick chicken is my favorite of the things I've tried. Overall great place with amazing food , but the waiting time is awful!
Amazing service, drinks and food
Nice place to take family to in the area. Not too rowdy on the weekends, comfortable with a homey feel.  Good burgers & ravioli. Good service
Suuuuper slow service, but there were only two people in the front of house and they were fairly busy. We all enjoyed our meals and they were very accommodating to challenging allergy.
We went for brunch on Saturday 7/27/19 and the food was great!  The waiter was friendly.  We didn’t have to wait long for our food.  I highly recommend Baron’s.  We will be back.

I took some friends from out of town here for dinner and was disappointed by the extremely slow service for unsatisfying portions of overpriced food. Despite the restaurant not being full, it took nearly an hour for our appetizer (a pitiful serving of calamari) to come out, and another 15 minutes thereafter for our entrees. A staff member assured us that the appetizers and entrees were going to come out together to minimize the time we had already waited, but this was clearly a lie. We also waited 10–15 minutes at the start for our drinks and clearly saw a large group of people at the bar being served their drinks before us. The burgers and sandwiches we ordered were not nearly satisfying enough to justify the high price, and one of the burgers that was ordered rare came much drier than expected. Shrimp risotto was good but was the exception to an otherwise poor execution of the whole meal. There was also burning smoke that started to fill the room a few minutes after we were seated, and the staff were not transparent at all about the source of the smoke. That likely contributed to the slower service in terms of food coming out on time, but that was not communicated clearly. I would not recommend this place in the future.
Really good food and good people. Wine pour could be better. Happy to see how much this place has grown. While you could do a walk-in for brunch one year ago, you need a reservation to get in now.
Food and drinks are delicious,great atmosphere and excellent service! I love the Cobb salad and the merguez omelette!
Really good food and good people. Wine pour could be better. Happy to see how much this place has grown. While you could do a walk-in for brunch one year ago, you need a reservation to get in now.
This often quiet Bed-Stuy gem, provides  excellent ambiance, service and cocktails, with heavenly offerings from their kitchen.
Great food, nice atmosphere. Perfect date night spot.

Good food, great service. If you like a little heat with your food, check out the hot sauce.
Delicious!!

This place had some of the worst food I have ever attempted to eat. We went for bottomless brunch. After calling and being told there was no wait, we were told there was a 20 minute wait when we arrived. 20 minutes turned into over and hour. When we finally did get to order, they were out of everything we tried to order. I settled on biscuits and gravy. The eggs were undercooked, and the gravy tasted like cream of hotdog soup. I’ve been in service industry for a long time, so I understand things don’t always go as planned, but this was ridiculous. Overall, it was extremely disappointing.
Great burger, tasty mixed drinks. More than expected items were unavailable though.

I love Baron's. The food is excellent and the staff is great, however, everytime I've gone there's always been a wait with the food, so I suggest you carve out a portion of your day to go. It will be worth the wait☺️
Food was great but like so many restaurants lately, service was the opposite. Took 45 min for soup. And 1 hour for the rest of the food. They need serious restaffing.
Service & Food great.
Great food, and I really liked the atmosphere/decor of the place. The service however, very friendly, but very, very slow.

I have a complicated opinion on this place. It's very out of the way unless you live in the area, but everything I ate was delicious and cooked to perfection, cocktails, orange blossom creme brulee, duck duo. My duck was both crispy and fall apart in my mouth, but the breast portion required a sharper knife than they gave me to cut the fat off of the edge. The environment is woody-heavy, with an interior section that appears like stained glass might in a warehouse district. Work and planning went into the ambiance and interior, but it's not cohesive and I'm not sure it works. They have board games, but they are missing pieces, and the addition of them muddles whatever vibe they are trying to create. Our server was friendly and informed, so no complaints there and the prices were standard for the quality and the area. I found their menu to be sadly small, but I reiterate, everything I ate was delicious - I have leftovers in my fridge I'll be eating today.

Delicious food in an out of the way spot.  Personally, I like mustard with my fries.... but Baron's serves Chinese mustard and I cannot hang with that. WAY too intense. Also, plates aren’t bad. You can serve your food on plates and people won’t hate you.

Heartwarming service from every single staff at this restaurant. Their beef burger patty is crispy outside juicy inside making the perfect balance. Fries are impeccable as well. Would love to come back.

Food is tasty, but a little tricky - banger and mash looks like the best deal on the menu until you realize they are up selling you on the second banger. Tasted good though. Reasonable french onion soup. PERFECTLY salted fries. Beer menu had almost no relationship to available beer, cocktails were weak and weakly flavored. Service friendly, but desultory. I might have been tempted to only give the place three stars, but the food really was delicious, the fries near perfect, and the ambiance a delightful surprise from the graffiti plastered cinderblock walls nearby.
Regulars now. Oysters are always shucked perfectly. Brussel sprouts salad is a must have. The brick chicken is delicious.  So is the salmon. But my absolute fav is the banger and mash.
Good for brunch. Never too busy.

The food was good but it took waaaaaay to long to get food and it wasn't even busy. It is a cozy spot and the customer service is good but I was soooo hungry and waited about an hour and a half for food.
Really delicious food, excellent wine, amazing service, beautiful environment, best music at the perfect volume. Overall a grand dinner experience! Will be back many times more!
This is a quality restaurant that is well run.
Good for brunch and even better for a romantic date. Food is delicious, the drinks are tasty and the decor is unique. Always have a good time at Baron's.
Food is great. Service is poor.  The FOH staff need to learn how to treat guest.
Overpriced

Come here pretty frequently. Good food and drinks. Just a little disappointed with a suggested tip situation last night that I hope can get sorted for future situations. I alerted our server to the issue, so I hope they resolved it.  On the itemized receipt you can see suggested tips are much higher than the customer copies. Maybe there’s a better explanation for this that I don’t understand. But 20% of $327.71 is not $78.40. It’s $65.54. That’s just wrong. Luckily I caught it and did the proper math. Just a heads up to future patrons to be more aware of.  Otherwise, food and drinks are still great here.
Delicious!

Worst NYE. They over booked, no customer service. My reservation was at 9:30pm and didn't sit till 10:30pm. No one approach us when we arrived, no one greeted up once we sat and we didn't get our entrees till midnight. Didn't even get welcomed into the bar while we waited an hour for our table. The chef walked out is what we were told, that's fine but no one in the front of the house took action regarding us waiting or offered us a drink. I asked for bread three times to eat something while we waited and never got it. Food was okay, espresso martini was good.
They serve good and delicious food
Amazing kitchen, conscientious serving team, & warm feeling environs...never had a bad meal here. The cocktails are consistent: twists on many clasics & genuinely creative.
Perfect place for brunch! The food was very good and the staff very nice. I recommend this restaurant if you're looking for a typical American brunch in a nice restaurant.

If you’re thinking about possibly coming here, you probably should. From start to finish, these people have got it DOWN. Honestly I think they’ve perfected every dish. Best restaurant I’ve been to in a veey long time. Also I never write reviews and here I am.

The only thing good about this place is the decor. The food was horrible. I got the burger ($17) and the fried chicken ($19). OVERPRICED! The chicken was weird. I asked for a well done burger and it was still rare the fries were too salty and the server didn't do anything about it. She was nice though.

Small but delicious menu. Nice vibes. Mostly blown away by the service. Our server Reginald (if I remember correctly- the man with beautiful eyes and long locks of hair, bright smile) was super professional and understanding of my friend and I taking a bit to order and staying for hours over our meal and drinks. Make a reservation on weekends! Music was good too!!!
Baron’s is fantastic. Great food. Great drinks..superb staff. Lovely business.
this is a great space with a cool bottomless brunch option. the food isn’t mind blowing but it’s fairly cheap with food service and it’s never crazy busy. You can definitely get in on a whim.

I had the house ground beef burger which was pretty big and also very good. My wife had the pressed chicken and she loved it (I tried a little and it was very good). If I had to choose between the two I'd probably go for the pressed chicken.
Great service. Nice space. Decent food. Good beer.

I loved what I ordered from here! I got the house ground beef burger, fries, and oysters. The oysters were a great starting point. The burger was perfectly seasoned. I could tell that the spices were mixed inside the meat before the patty was shaped. Tripped me out because I haven't had a burger like that in a long time. The fries were sooo good!  You'd definitely enjoy Baron's ambiance. It was warm and cozy the night I went. Not too many people were at the bar so my friend and I got plenty of attention. I was definitely impressed as a first-timer!

If you haven't been to Barons, you better put it on your list. The decor and overall ambiance when you walk in is wonderful. Always playing great music.  The service is fast, attentive and incredibly friendly. And the food makes it difficult to go anywhere else for dinner.  Flatbread specials and oysters are a must have appetizer and anything on the menu is a treat.  Plus for dessert, they have boozy ice cream.  Irish cream was my  personal favorite but they have several flavors.  I simply cannot compliment this place enough. Love it.

Overpriced and grossly underserved orange juice. They give you a glass slightly larger than a shot glass. It is absolutely ridiculous. As a matter of fact, while there, someone else ordered the orange juice, but to go, not to stay. When the server went behind the bar to serve the glass, she then poured it into a plastic to-go cup, which literally filled less than half the cup. This is not a joke.

Awesome experience.  Friendly staff, great music (not too loud), excellent food.  I loved their Vegan Bean and Mushroom Burger!  Ambiance  was perfect (soft lighting and comfortable spacing  between tables).
Great, low key brunch.

The food is fantastic! So are the prices.  I've been to this place several times, had different food, and it was always great. The place is hardly ever full, so it's nice and quiet. Reservations are easy to get. I usually get exactly the time I wish for.  Easy to spot from the street. Has a nice vibe to it.  I know, I sound like I work sales for them. I don't. I just really like this place :)
The food was ok. But the pilgrims drink was the best.

Good spot with a nice atmosphere, tasty food, friendly bartender (though not overly knowledgeable). Draft beer selection is small but they have some bottles as well as other drinks. Would definitely go back.
The brunch dishes were quite tasty and you can easily tell that everything was house-made using high quality ingredients.  I only wish the portion sizes were a tad larger to match the hefty tab.

This place was outstanding. Happened by while walking through the neighborhood and stopped in for a bite and drink. The server was most excellent and the food, so tasty. It's a cozy atmosphere that's very welcoming. Give em a try, you'll love it.

Great bartender, waitress, and hostess tonight! Cool spot and nice use of space. I like the detective looking door hanging sodeways above the bar. Went for drinks and dessert. Delicious chocolate lava cake or something like and creme brulee. I got a veggie burger w fries a couple years ago and I remember it being good. Will def go another time for din and probably get dessert, too. I'd say it's a good date spot, larger party, or family place. Good for any occasion, really.

Awesome brunch place in Brooklyn.
Very good place and great ppl!

I ended up here on my birthday after having to leave another nearby restaurant due to them having kitchen issues. I was pleasantly surprised with this hidden gem I found off the beaten path. The food was amazing and they even comped me a surprise birthday dessert after hearing it was my birthday.
Great food. Great drinks. Great service! A cute happy hour and atmosphere for dates.
Great brunch. Great Drinks. Highly recommend the french press coffee. Service was outstanding also. Would definitely go back. Also very modestly priced imo.
Good vibe. Nice and dark, pretty romantic if you need it to be. Kitchen knows what they are doing. Great menu. Specials are hit or miss.

Went for brunch. Good but I took off a star because there's only one vegan option: a vegan burger. I made another dish work for me by subbing/omitting some animal products. But there really needs to be more on the menu.
It was one of the loveliest dinner dates I had. Decor 5 stars!  food&service as well
Pretty little gem in Bed-stuy. The staff was super friendly and helpful. The place is really cute and the musix was good. The food was pretty good. I recommend.
Great food
Cute little spot with a friendly staff that has great food. Recently went for brunch - food and service was on point! Highly recommend to anyone in that neighborhood!
Always wonderful atmosphere, amazing food, and beautiful sustainable design.
can't say enough good things about this place. service, food, ambiance... they come together to make an amazing experience for brunch AND dinner
Great bar, great food, and just a really friendly place!

Barons has one of the best burgers in Brooklyn. Bartender Ash and server Nick are phenomenal. They always accommodate me and anyone that I bring in. The owners are frequently present and sociable. Every aspect of this space makes me want to return, which I do, frequently.
Typical hipster Brooklyn restaurant with all of the "rustic" touches. The brick pressed chicken was amazing. Will try again. Prices are nice. Waiter was nice and attentive.
The food is delicious. Love the brunch menu. The burger and breakfast sandwich are hands down delicious!! Great service, staff makes you feel like home each time you visit. Love them!!
Wonderful food
This place has a nice layout. We had our staff holiday dinner here and the food was great. Nice chill vibe but they also put the music up towards the end.
Love Ash! The food is down to earth home cooking and the vibe is always on point!
Ordered oysters and a burger, the oysters took 35 minutes to come out. After being there for 45 minutes and still no burger, I paid for the oysters and left.

I visited Baron's for dinner and I was very impressed. The service and food were both excellent. I'll definitely be returning again. The burger and brick pressed chicken we're delicious and I look forward to trying the other menu items.

What a gem of a discovery.. Service...personal,inteligent, fun but knowledgable Food....perfect started with some oysters, then had a nightly special Fried Chicken with mashed potatoes gravy...chicken so crisp but perfectly moist...wife  had pasta safron and shrimp  New favorite
Great food offers here... Go and enjoy with friends
Fantastic food ,great service a great neighborhood spot!
I'm 50/50 on this place. I've had both great and mediocre meals here but lean on the optimistic side. Always great oysters and drinks
Excellent bar, food and staff!

Went here for brunch with the family.  Very quiet place with good music playing in the background.  Pricing is right and the mimosas were on point.  Waitress was very kind and attentive.  Another spot to add to my places to go when I go to Bed-Stuy
Food is amazing, atmosphere too. Cocktails are run of the mill. Make sure you go when Doomy is working, great bartender.

Warm atmosphere, cool decor with rustic touches, the nice waitress let me know that everything was recycled. The doors, Windows, mirrors and church pews all made for an interesting look. The food was a good serving and tasty!
Great. 100% recommended
I had tje biscuits and gravy. There was practically no gravy on it. Pretty disappointing.
Since it came under new ownership, the food is incredible
Nice brunch
Great staff, beautiful cozy atmosphere. happy hour from 5-7  offers $1 oysters.

Great food, great service. Beef tar tar could probably use more than 3 pieces of toast. But that being said good cocktails and I guess Sundays have live music which is nice. Interesting decor for sure.
Do not get the French Toast, it was literally so disgusting that I took two bites and pretended that I got called into work so I could leave and not offend anyone.

We were almost the only ones there but still service was slow. No water refills and even when asked for one they forgot. Burgers took over half hour to arrive and was quite small but qas good. Seafood pasta was expensive and tasted bad.

A great menu, with great food. An inviting warm atmosphere. The decor is awesome with reclaimed church pews and old doctors office doors. Walls lined with Old windows. It's really a cool place. Usually have some interesting cocktails and a local brewery on tap. Brunch menu is awesome. Happy hour everyday from 5-7pm with dollar oysters. This can't really be beat.
I went to this place when I first opened so perhaps things have changed but I thought it was a little overpriced for the area and the food wasn't that great
Great food.  Vintage decor.
Live Jazz brunch is 👌🏿
The burger was mediocre. The decor is unique

What a treat. You can tell this chef loves and knows food. Incredible flavors mixed with such love and precision. Real high quality food. Even the vegan dishes  are sensational. Tasteful decor, good people.
Great food and drinks. Not too far from the subway. Great rustic ambiance and friendly staff.

This is a great new addition to the neighborhood!  Went here last night and had incredibly fresh and tasty oysters--the best I've had in NYC--along with great steak and beef tar tar.  The checkmate cocktail is also fantastic--really nice old school vibe at an affordable price!
GREAT food and super friendly staff.. Welcome to the neighborhood :)
